[i][size=14pt]Server[/size][/i][size=7pt]
This isn't no 'old school remake,' although it does have the look & feel to it. This server is [b]SQL BASED[/b]! 
[b]Player saving and loading is done via SQL[/b], it is NOT recommended running a source like this connected to a virtual host unless it's from the same computer it's running on!
I made the server to work with the [b][url=http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php?topic=564369.0]RuneScape Community Script[/url][/b]. I've programmed the server to work with the site, well like share thing with each other.. The RCS script that i'm using it modified by a lot by [i]me[/i].

The server does require a registered account on the site to play! There is NO CONNECTION TO THE DATABASE between this time of checking wether the player is registered or not!
Sounds weird, but well, the checking is done from the website, as seen in one of Martin's tutorial

[img]http://dl.dropbox.com/u/66646093/RuneScape/RSPS/474%20SQL/images/Screen%20Shot%202012-10-18%20at%202.55.12%20PM.png[/img]

Another neat thing i've added was the Login Screen checkings! Since the RSC Website Script comes with a full functional Recovery system, message centre and forums, it was very easy integrating it to the server: Unread private [b]message from the site[/b], and [u]seen in game[/u]
